    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty ride, and honestly, it\u2019s been such a joy to drive. It\u2019s in really solid shape\u2014super reliable, clean, and has plenty of life left in it! I\u2019ve taken great care of it, so it\u2019s ready for someone new to jump in and start their next adventure. Whether you\u2019re commuting or hitting the road for the weekend, this car won\u2019t let you down. It's been a total gem for me, and I'm sure you'll love it too. Come take it for a spin and see for yourself!",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 18
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a driver-spec E46 M3 powered by the high-revving S54B32 inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This example is mechanically sorted, with the essential subframe reinforcement completed and the dual-VANOS system recently serviced to ensure precise valve timing. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory M Variable Differential Lock. The suspension geometry remains true with refreshed bushings, offering the telepathic turn-in these chassis are known for. While showing minor cosmetic character from regular use, the drivetrain is stout and the throttle response remains razor-sharp. A mechanically sound, analog performance machine ready for the canyons.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
